# Web Architecture

## Layer Flow

```
routes â†’ modules â†’ @primer-guidy/components-web (atoms/molecules/organisms/templates)
                 â†’ @primer/react (direct Primer components)
                 â†’ services (promises + hooks + types)
```

## Web App Directory Structure

Web apps contain ONLY app-specific code. NO `components/` directory â€” all UI components come from the shared design system.

```
src/
  routes/          â†’ Route definitions only (TanStack Router)
  modules/         â†’ Feature orchestrators (compose DS components + services)
  services/        â†’ Data layer (promises, hooks, types â€” single source of truth)
  i18n/            â†’ Internationalization config + locale files per namespace
  utils/           â†’ App-specific pure helpers (NO SVG icons â€” icons live in components-web/atoms/Icons)
  hooks/           â†’ App-specific custom hooks (non-service)
  context/         â†’ React Context providers for app-level DI
  styles/          â†’ Reusable SCSS utilities (breakpoints, mixins)
  test/            â†’ Test setup and utilities
```

## Design System (`apps/components-web/`)

All reusable UI components AND shared utilities live in the shared design system package:

```
src/
  components/      â†’ Atomic Design: atoms/, molecules/, organisms/, templates/
  hooks/           â†’ Shared React hooks (useSubscription, etc.)
  stores/          â†’ Shared UI state (Zustand stores consumed by components)
  styles/          â†’ Shared SCSS utilities (breakpoints)
  utils/           â†’ Shared utilities (buildThemeVars, PrimerColors, etc.)
  test/            â†’ Test setup
  index.ts         â†’ Public API â€” all exports go through here
```

### Shared Utilities in `components-web`

Utilities needed by multiple web apps (e.g., `buildThemeVars`, `PrimerColors`) MUST live in `components-web/src/utils/` and be exported from `index.ts`. NEVER duplicate utilities across apps.

### `AppProviders` â€” Standard Root Layout

`AppProviders` (in `components-web/src/components/templates/AppProviders/`) wraps the full provider stack: QueryClientProvider, ThemeProvider, BaseStyles, CloudServicesProvider, and themed CSS variables. ALL web apps MUST use it in `__root.tsx`:

```tsx
// __root.tsx â€” minimal and consistent across all apps
import { createCloudServicesFromEnv } from '@primer-guidy/cloud-services'
import { AppProviders } from '@primer-guidy/components-web'

const cloudServices = createCloudServicesFromEnv({ /* env vars */ })

function RootLayout() {
  const { queryClient } = Route.useRouteContext()
  return (
    <AppProviders queryClient={queryClient} cloudServices={cloudServices}>
      <Outlet />
    </AppProviders>
  )
}
```

NEVER manually nest QueryClientProvider, ThemeProvider, BaseStyles, or CloudServicesProvider â€” use `AppProviders`.

## Layer Responsibilities

### `routes/`

Two distinct roles:

**`__root.tsx` â€” Composition Root (single injection point)**
- The ONLY place in the app that wires providers and cloud services
- Imports from `@primer-guidy/cloud-services`, `@primer-guidy/components-web`, and `@tanstack/react-router`
- Creates `cloudServices` instance and wraps `<AppProviders>`
- This is the single level of injection â€” modules and components NEVER know where services come from

**All other route files â€” Route Definitions only**
- ONLY `createFileRoute` + import from `modules/`
- NEVER contain UI logic or business logic

```tsx
// routes/dashboard.tsx
import { createFileRoute } from '@tanstack/react-router'
import { Dashboard } from '@/modules/Dashboard'

export const Route = createFileRoute('/dashboard')({
  component: Dashboard,
})
```

### `modules/`
- Feature orchestrators â€” compose UI + data
- Import components from `@primer-guidy/components-web` or `@primer/react`
- Import hooks/types from `services/`
- Each module follows the standard component file structure
- Modules are the ONLY consumer of service hooks

### Components (in `@primer-guidy/components-web`)
- Pure UI only â€” NO data fetching, NO service imports
- Receive data via props (types from `services/`)
- Exception: `useTranslation` is allowed in components (see i18n rule)
- Web apps NEVER have their own `components/` directory

### `services/`
- Single source of truth for ALL types and data access
- Types (Response, Request, Payload) are the contracts used everywhere
- Validation schemas (valibot) live in service types (see forms-validation rule)
- See services-layer rule for full structure

## Import Rules

- `routes/__root.tsx` â†’ imports from `@primer-guidy/cloud-services`, `@primer-guidy/components-web`, `@tanstack/react-router` (composition root)
- `routes/*` (all other) â†’ imports from `modules/` ONLY
- `modules/` â†’ imports from `@primer-guidy/components-web`, `@primer/react`, `services/`, and `utils/`
- `@primer-guidy/components-web` â†’ imports from `@primer/react` and internal components only (+ `useTranslation`)
- `services/` â†’ imports from `utils/` and shared `libs/`
- NEVER circular dependencies between layers
- Web apps NEVER import from a local `components/` or `stores/` directory â€” use `@primer-guidy/components-web`
